msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Cmulti-tenant-portal.md:31
msgid ""
"The frontend reads the `municipality` claim from the JWT on login and "
"applies the corresponding theme by setting CSS custom properties on "
"`document.documentElement`:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Cmulti-tenant-portal.md:33
msgid ""
"--color-primary\n"
"--color-primary-dark\n"
"--color-primary-light\n"
"--color-secondary\n"
"--color-accent"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Cmulti-tenant-portal.md:41
msgid ""
"This means a single deployed frontend binary serves all municipalities — the "
"branding switches per user session based on their JWT claim, with no page "
"reload required."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cfeatures%5Cmulti-tenant-portal.md:43
msgid ""
"The tenant configuration is loaded from `public/tenants.json` at runtime. "
"Each entry specifies the theme, the municipality code (for API filtering), "
"enabled features, and contact details."
msgstr ""

